<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>iswblank
</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
test for whitespace wide character
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<DATE>13 April 2001</DATE>
</REFSYNOPSISDIVINFO>
<FUNCSYNOPSIS>
<FUNCSYNOPSISINFO>
#include &lt;wctype.h&gt;
</FUNCSYNOPSISINFO>
<FUNCPROTOTYPE>
 <FUNCDEF>int 
  <FUNCTION>iswblank</FUNCTION></FUNCDEF>
 <PARAMDEF>wint_t 
  <PARAMETER><REPLACEABLE>wc</REPLACEABLE></PARAMETER></PARAMDEF>
</FUNCPROTOTYPE>
</FUNCSYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<REFSECT1INFO>
<DATE>13 April 2001</DATE>
</REFSECT1INFO>
<TITLE>Description
</TITLE>
<PARA>
<FUNCTION>iswblank</FUNCTION> is the wide-character equivalent of 
<FUNCTION>isblank</FUNCTION>. It tests whether <PARAMETER>wc</PARAMETER> 
is a wide character belonging to the wide character class "blank".
</PARA>
<PARA>
The wide character class <EMPHASIS>blank</EMPHASIS> is a subclass of 
the wide character class <EMPHASIS>space</EMPHASIS>, and is therefore
disjoint from the wide character class <EMPHASIS>graph</EMPHASIS>.
<EMPHASIS>blank</EMPHASIS> is also therefore disjoint from the
<EMPHASIS>graph</EMPHASIS> subclasses <EMPHASIS>alnum</EMPHASIS>, 
<EMPHASIS>alpha</EMPHASIS>, <EMPHASIS>upper</EMPHASIS>, 
<EMPHASIS>lower</EMPHASIS>, <EMPHASIS>digit</EMPHASIS>, 
<EMPHASIS>xdigit</EMPHASIS>, and <EMPHASIS>punct</EMPHASIS>.
</PARA>
<PARA>
The wide character class <EMPHASIS>blank</EMPHASIS> always contains 
at least the <TOKEN>SPACE</TOKEN> character and the control character 
<TOKEN>\t</TOKEN>.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Return Value
</TITLE>
<PARA>
If <PARAMETER>wc</PARAMETER> is a wide character belonging
to the wide character class <EMPHASIS>blank</EMPHASIS>, a 
non-<LITERAL>ZERO</LITERAL> value is returned. Otherwise, 
<RETURNVALUE>0</RETURNVALUE> is returned. 
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Notes
</TITLE>
<PARA>
The behavior of <FUNCTION>iswblank</FUNCTION> depends on the 
<VARNAME>LC_CTYPE</VARNAME> category of the current locale.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>
